1 mani festations of antisemitism are directed toward Jewish or non-
2 Jewish individuals or their property, toward Jewish community
3 institutions and religious facilities. For the purposes of this
4 section, Oklahoma adopts the working definition and examples of
5 antisemitism by the IHRA;
6 2. “Discriminatory practice” means a practice designated as
7 discriminatory under the terms of this act;
8 2. 3. “Equal”, with reference to sex as defined in Section 16
9 of this title, shall not be construed to mean same or identical, and
10 to differentiate between the sexes shall not necessarily be
11 construed to be treating the sexes unequally;
12 3. 4. “National origin” includes the national origin of an
13 ancestor; and
14 4. 5. “Person” includes an individual, association,
15 corporation, joint apprenticeship committee, joint-stock company,
16 labor union, legal representative, mutual company, partnership,
17 receiver, trust, trustee, trustee in bankruptcy, unincorporated
18 organization, any other legal or commercial entity, the state, or
19 any governmental entity or agency.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
